{"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/snapshotmanager"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SnapshotManager","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"SnapshotManager","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" provides save, restore, list, and delete","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"operations for VM snapshots. Each snapshot is a full copy of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the VM’s disk image (","type":"text"},{"code":"disk.img","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") and auxiliary storage","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(","type":"text"},{"code":"auxiliary.bin","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"), stored in a named subdirectory under the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"bundle’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"SavedStates\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" directory.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"How-Snapshots-Work","text":"How Snapshots Work"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Unlike VZ state save (which captures in-memory VM state and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"requires the VM to be running in the same process),","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"disk-level snapshots copy the on-disk artifacts. This means:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The VM ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"must be stopped","type":"text"}]},{"text":" before saving or restoring.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Snapshots work across processes and reboots.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Restoring replaces the current disk and auxiliary storage","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with the snapshot copies.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"APFS-Copy-on-Write","text":"APFS Copy-on-Write"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On APFS volumes, both save and restore use ","type":"text"},{"code":"FileManager.copyItem","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"which the system maps to ","type":"text"},{"code":"clonefile(2)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". This produces a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"copy-on-write clone instead of a byte-for-byte copy, making","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"snapshot creation and restoration near-instantaneous regardless","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of disk image size. Only blocks that diverge after the clone","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"consume additional storage.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Snapshot-Directory-Layout","text":"Snapshot Directory Layout"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["my-vm.vm\/","├── disk.img","├── auxiliary.bin","├── ...","└── SavedStates\/","    ├── clean-install\/","    │   ├── disk.img","    │   ├── auxiliary.bin","    │   └── snapshot-info.json","    └── before-xcode\/","        ├── disk.img","        ├── auxiliary.bin","        └── snapshot-info.json"],"syntax":null},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Example","text":"Example"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let bundle = try VirtualMachineBundle.load(from: bundleURL)","","\/\/ Save a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.save(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")","","\/\/ List snapshots","let snapshots = try SnapshotManager.list(bundle: bundle)","for snap in snapshots {","    print(\"\\(snap.label): \\(snap.sizeInBytes) bytes\")","}","","\/\/ Restore a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.restore(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")","","\/\/ Delete a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.delete(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")"],"syntax":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager"},"metadata":{"title":"SnapshotManager","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SnapshotManager","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit15SnapshotManagerO","symbolKind":"enum","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SnapshotManager"}],"roleHeading":"Enumeration","role":"symbol"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Snapshots","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotInfo","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotError"],"generated":true,"title":"Snapshots"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Manages disk-level snapshots for virtual machine bundles.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Type-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/infoFileName","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/savedStatesDirectory"],"generated":true,"title":"Type Properties"},{"anchor":"Type-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/delete(bundle:label:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/list(bundle:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/restore(bundle:label:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/save(bundle:label:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Type Methods"}],"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/SnapshotManager/resto